comment:
* Holds information related to DisplayPort Alt Mode statuses
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: DISPLAYPORT_ALT_MODE_STATUS_UNKNOWN
variables.comment:
* Port Partners: * The port partner status is currently unknown for one of the following reasons: *
    *
  • No port partner is connected to the device *
  • The USB Power Delivery Discover Identity command has not been issued to the port * partner via SOP messaging. *
*

* Cables: * The cable’s capabilities are not yet known to the device, or no cable is plugged in.

variables.name: DISPLAYPORT_ALT_MODE_STATUS_NOT_CAPABLE
variables.comment:
* Port Partners: * The current port partner does not list DisplayPort as one of its Alt Modes, or does not list * the capability to act as a DisplayPort Source or Sink device, or a compatible configuration * could not be established. *

* Cables: * The cable/adapter’s capabilities do not list DisplayPort as one of its Alt Modes, or a * compatible configuration could not be established.

variables.name: DISPLAYPORT_ALT_MODE_STATUS_CAPABLE_DISABLED
variables.comment:
* Port Partners: * The current port partner lists compatible DisplayPort capabilities with the device, however * may not yet have entered DisplayPort Alt Mode or has configured its port for data * transmission. *

* Cables: * The Type-C cable/adapter’s capabilities have been discovered and list DisplayPort Alt Mode * as one of its capabilities, however may not yet have entered DisplayPort Alt Mode or has been * configured for data transmission.

variables.name: DISPLAYPORT_ALT_MODE_STATUS_ENABLED
variables.comment:
* Port Partners: * The port partner and device are both configured for DisplayPort Alt Mode. *

* Cables: * The Type-C cable/adapter is configured for DisplayPort Alt Mode.

variables.name: LINK_TRAINING_STATUS_UNKNOWN
variables.comment: * Indicates that DisplayPort Alt Mode link training has not initiated or completed.

variables.name: LINK_TRAINING_STATUS_SUCCESS
variables.comment:
* Indicates that DisplayPort Alt Mode link training has completed and the optimal data
     * transmission settings between the device and the connected port partner have successfully
     * been negotiated.

variables.name: LINK_TRAINING_STATUS_FAILURE
variables.comment:
* Indicates that DisplayPort Alt Mode link training has completed but no data transmission
     * settings between the device and the connected port partner could be established, and that the
     * link initialization has terminated.

methods.name: public int getPartnerSinkStatus()
methods.comment:
* Returns the DisplayPort Alt Mode Status for a port partner acting as a sink.
     *

methods.name: public int getCableStatus()
methods.comment:
* Returns the DisplayPort Alt Mode Status for the attached cable
     *

methods.name: public int getNumberOfLanes()
methods.comment:
* Returns the number of lanes used to transmit display data.
     *

methods.name: public boolean isHotPlugDetectActive()
methods.comment:
* Returns whether or not the Hot Plug Detect (HPD) value of the connected DisplayPort Alt Mode
     * partner sink is active.

methods.name: public int getLinkTrainingStatus()
methods.comment: * Returns the DisplayPort Alt Mode link training status.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
